Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses social collaboration graphs and their convexity, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The concept of convex subgraphs and measures of network convexity are related to graph theory and algorithms, which are covered in this sub-category. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses spatial infrastructure networks, which are a type of network architecture. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The study of network properties and their applications can be related to software engineering, which is covered in this sub-category. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The concept of convexity is related to computational geometry, which is covered in this sub-category.
